# üå§Ô∏è Weather App

A simple and interactive **Weather App** built using **HTML**, **CSS**, and **JavaScript**.  
This app allows users to search for any city and instantly view the **current temperature**, **weather condition**, and a **weather icon**, powered by the **OpenWeatherMap API**.

---

## Project Overview

This project was created as part of a web development activity to demonstrate:
- Clear and clean **HTML + CSS structure**
- **JavaScript interactivity** and logical API integration
- Practical use of **real-world data** through an external API

---

## Features

- Search weather by city name  
- Displays city, temperature, and weather description  
- Shows weather icons dynamically  
- Real-time data using OpenWeatherMap API  
- Clean, responsive, and minimal design  

---

## Technologies Used

- HTML5: Structure and layout
- CSS3: Styling and responsiveness
- JavaScript: Logic, interactivity, API handling
- OpenWeatherMap API: Provides live weather data

---

## how to run the app

- Open index.html in your web browser
- Enter a city name and click Search
(e.g., cities to try: Mumbai, London, Paris, New York, Sydney, Bengaluru, Delhi, Tokyo ect)

